INSERT INTO TranslatedTexts(id, language, textValue) VALUES (479, 'en-UK', 'Integrated Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering');
INSERT INTO TranslatedTexts(id, language, textValue) VALUES (480, 'en-UK', 'The teaching of Computer Engineering and Computing at FEUP was designed as a complete five-year integrated training and learning cycle, corresponding to the 1st and 2nd cycles of the Bologna Process implementation and immediately awarding the Master''s degree. At the end of the first three years (1st cycle) of the MIEIC, students will have a solid basic training, covering essential scientific and engineering skills, as well as fundamental broad-band knowledge in the various areas of computer science, although without any specialization. This first step is seen mainly as an enabler of mobility to and from other national and European schools. At the end of the five-year course, graduates will have advanced training in Computer Engineering and Computing, and may have chosen an area of specialization or maintained a wider range of interests, thanks to a wide range of options, individually configurable, contained in the study plan. The possible specializations currently include: - Software Engineering and Information Systems (2 sub-areas with these names) - Networks and Information Technologies (sub-areas of Internet Technologies and Computer Infrastructures) - Intelligent and Multimedia Systems (2 sub-areas with these names)');
INSERT INTO TranslatedTexts(id, language, textValue) VALUES (481, 'en-UK', 'The main objective of the Bachelor''s Degree in Computer Engineering is to provide future graduates with the basic principles, theories, methods and practices of Computer Engineering and Computing so that they can master all the concepts for their intervention in society or complement their training with the 2nd cycle following practical life or the scientific career. To achieve this general objective, the study cycle aims to reconcile the following specific objectives: instrumental, systemic and interpersonal. - At the instrumental level, it is sought that graduates in Computer Engineering acquire skills to harmoniously articulate the complementarity between analysis and synthesis, that they internalize the dynamics of problem solving, that they learn the logics and practices of information management and that they perspective the exercise of these skills according to organizational planning approaches focused on building value for the client and transforming complexity into performance. - At the systemic level, it is sought to strengthen their autonomy and capacity to learn, their adaptability to new situations, their projective sense in the application of knowledge and skills and their acculturation to quality and excellence. - Finally, at the interpersonal level, it is sought that students acquire other types of skills, which contribute to the development of the personal and civic side, the ability to acquire knowledge autonomously, critical and responsible sense, information management, teamwork and in interdisciplinary teams, collective learning and the sense of body in the construction of success, etc. The Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering (MEI) proposes four areas of specialization according to the latest curricular recommendations of the Association for Computer Machinery (ACM) and the Institute for Electrical and Electronic Engineers (IEEE): - Communications, Services and Infrastructures - Intelligent Systems - Information Systems - Software Engineering. It is thus proposed to create specializations to meet the needs of the market, both at the level of industry and services, and at the level of research, aiming at an international impact in the medium term.');
INSERT INTO TranslatedTexts(id, language, textValue) VALUES (482, 'en-UK', 'The Bachelor''s Degree in Computer Engineering and Computer Science (LEIC) is one of the largest undergraduate degrees at Técnico and has already proven its success in the job market, both nationally and internationally. LEIC graduates are recognized as competent professionals with solid knowledge in computer engineering and easy adaptability to the constant evolution of information technologies. At the end of the LEIC, the student may specialize in one of the areas offered in the Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering and Computer Science at Técnico, in another related course, or even enter the job market. The Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering and Computer Science is based on the strong foundation provided by the first cycle, offers attractive specializations for students and the market, also serving as a basis for students who wish to enter a PhD program, and creates a solid basis for the intervention of the Department of Computer Engineering at IST in lifelong learning, which will represent an increasingly important component of the advanced education market. At the end of the Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering and Computer Science, students will be able to enter the job market. Taking into account the specializations mentioned above, students have a wide range of specific professional skills, of which the following stand out: - Analysis and design of complex systems - Systems project management techniques - Modeling and use of data in computer systems - Development of applications in distributed systems - Management, configuration and operation of computer systems - Advanced problem solving techniques - Design of adaptable systems for solving complex problems - Design of systems that interact with humans using natural interfaces - Control and robotics - Modeling and control of industrial systems - Generic optimization techniques Typical employers for engineers who have completed the Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering and Computer Science at IST, Alameda campus, are the following: banking and insurance services companies, IT services providers, telecommunications companies, software development companies.');
INSERT INTO TranslatedTexts(id, language, textValue) VALUES (483, 'en-UK', 'The Bachelor''s Degree in Computer Engineering at the University of Aveiro aims to provide a solid education in computer engineering, an area that has been revealed as the main engine of development in advanced economies. More specifically, this degree aims to provide the following skills: - Understand and use software development methodologies in small and large scale projects. - Plan and write correct, robust, efficient, well-organized and well-documented programs. - Understand and use models and abstractions in the design, implementation and use of computational and information systems. - Understand the fundamental aspects of computer architecture and operating systems, and their importance in the development and execution of computer applications. - Apply knowledge in the areas of calculus, probability, statistics and discrete mathematics to computer science problems. - Apply quality assessment and management techniques in Computer Engineering projects. - Communicate effectively and be able to work in multidisciplinary teams. - Recognize the need for, and have the ability to, actively engage in a continuous lifelong learning process. The objectives of the Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering are aligned with this strategy and with the needs of the market, aiming to: - Provide the regional, national and international business fabric with qualified high-level staff; - Promote advanced training focused on innovation, development and research in computer engineering.');
INSERT INTO TranslatedTexts(id, language, textValue) VALUES (484, 'en-UK', 'The Integrated Master''s Degree in Computer Engineering (MiEI) is an integrated course of the first and second cycles of higher education, taught at the University of Minho, with a duration of 5 academic years, 10 academic semesters, 40 weeks of full-time study per year and a total of 300 ECTS. The MiEI aims to prepare computer engineers, capable of all the phases currently recognized in the rigorous process of analysis, design and implementation of computer solutions. Its graduates should acquire during the course great theoretical and practical experience in the analysis of software systems, in the specification of the requirements of these systems, in the techniques of prototype construction and in all phases of their installation, in the management of computer projects, in the testing, installation and maintenance of computer applications, and, consequently, of the systems or networks that support them. The MiEI has as its basic objective to provide its students during the course with the expertise and knowledge (theoretical and practical) necessary for: - The analysis and specification of requirements of software systems to be implemented; - The application of prototype construction techniques; - The design, conception, development, testing and maintenance of computer applications; - The implementation of computer communication networks and support infrastructures; - The management and implementation of computer projects, including the design and implementation of computer systems. As future engineers, they should also always be concerned with rigor, both in the execution and management of the project, evaluating its quality, costs and economic impact, as well as in the concerns of implementing their products in the target organizations.');
